00014 /*
00015     QMI REQUEST PACKET SENT OVER IPC CHANNEL AND RECEIVED BY QMRR TASK
00016     -------------------------------------------
00017     | QMUXSDU PREAMBLE  | QMI SERVICE MESSAGE |
00018     -------------------------------------------
00019 bytes:      7               m
00020 
00021     QMUX SDU PREAMBLE
00022     -------------------------------------------------------------------
00023     | QMI Service Type | QMI Request Timeout | QMI Transaction Length |
00024     -------------------------------------------------------------------
00025 bytes:      1               4                           2
00026 
00027     QMI SERVICE MESSAGE
00028     --------------------------------------
00029     | QMI SVC MSG HDR | QMI SVC MSG TLVs |
00030     --------------------------------------
00031 bytes:      4               n
00032 
00033     QMI SVC MSG HDR
00034     ------------------------
00035     | MSG ID  | MSG LENGTH |
00036     ------------------------
00037 bytes:   2          2
00038 
00039 */
00040

00075 /**********************
00076  *  QMUX SDU DEFINES  *
00077  **********************/
00078 /* The preamble contains any data the SDK QM task requires to carry out the QMI
00079  * request that does not form the QMI (request) Message sent to the device.
00080  * Current preamble fields include:
00081  *  QMI service pertaining to th QMI request (swi_uint8)
00082  *  QMI request timeout (swi_uint32)
00083  *  QMI Transaction length (swi_uint16)
00084  */
00085 #define QMUXSDU_PREAMBLE    7
00086 
00087 /* QMI Parameter field (QMUX SDU) maximum size */
00088 #define QMPARAMMAX          4 * 1024
00089 
00090 /*** QMI Protocol Field definitions ***/

00092 /* QMI Service Message definitions */
00093 #define QMISVC_MSGID_SZ             2   /* QMI service message, message ID size */
00094 #define QMISVC_MSGLENSZ             2   /* QMI service message, message length */
00095 #define QMISVC_MSGHDR_SZ            (QMISVC_MSGID_SZ + QMISVC_MSGLENSZ)
00096 #define QMISVC_MSGID_OFFSET         0
00097 #define QMISVC_MSGLEN_OFFSET        (QMISVC_MSGID_OFFSET + QMISVC_MSGID_SZ)
00098 
00099 /* QMI Service Transaction (QMUX SDU) definitions */
00100 #define QMUXSDU_CTRLFLGS_SZ         1   /* QMI service transaction control flags size */
00101 #define QMUXSDU_XACTIONID_SZ        2   /* QMI service transaction transaction ID size */
00102 #define QMUXSDU_HDR_SZ              (QMUXSDU_CTRLFLGS_SZ +\
00103                                      QMUXSDU_XACTIONID_SZ)
00104 
00105 #define QMUXSDU_CTRLFLGS_OFFSET     0
00106 #define QMUXSDU_XACTIONID_OFFSET    (QMUXSDU_CTRLFLGS_OFFSET +\
00107                                      QMUXSDU_CTRLFLGS_SZ)
00108 #define QMUXSDU_QMISVCMSG_OFFSET    (QMUXSDU_XACTIONID_OFFSET +\
00109                                      QMUXSDU_XACTIONID_SZ)
00110 
00111 /* QMI TLV definitions */
00112 #define QMITLV_TYPE_SZ               1   /* QMI TLV, type size */
00113 #define QMITLV_LENGTH_SZ             2   /* QMI TLV,  TLV length */
00114 #define QMITLV_HDR_SZ                (QMITLV_TYPE_SZ + QMITLV_LENGTH_SZ)
00115 
00116 /* Invalid QMI transaction ID */
00117 #define QMI_TRANSACTION_ID_INVALID   0
00118 #define QMI_MSG_ID_INVALID          -1
